@piquark6046 , @Alex-302 , since the [1815 issue](https://github.com/AdguardTeam/CoreLibs/issues/1815) was fixed (at least for me), everything is not working again.
But, I hope, I found a (temporary) workaround: when this QUIC issue was active, there was the Google certificate on YouTube, but there were no ads or overlays, so, I think, AdGuard DNS filtered out all ads. Now I can observe the same behaviour in private Firefox windows: Google certificates, no overlays and no ads.
So, I think, you can incorporate this "solution" at least for now: just don't inject the AdGuard certificate to YouTube, filter it only with the AdGuard DNS.

